begin{notes}


Infantry.  [2,1].  Marches around and captures things.  A VERY good
first unit.

Armor.  [14,7].  Rolls around 2 hexes/turn, captures things better,
kill things better than infantry.

Special forces.  [14,9].  Invisible scout.  Moves 1 hex/turn on any
terrain, 2 hex/turn on plains and desert.  Very poor offense, defense just
worse than infantry.  Builds base in 12 turns.  Fits on most boats.
Can capture some enemy units and take them for your side.

Air Transport [12,8]  Carries lots of money, carries 1X, carries
2i, carries lots of mines, carries 1a.

Fighter.  [16,8].  Carries missiles, munches on bombers and other
aircraft.

Attack helicopter.  [10,5]  Stomps on infantry/armor units, good for
minesweeping.

Bomber.  [23,15].  Hits bases and cities hard, carries an infantry,
and nukes, and missiles.

Destroyer.  [20,15].  Carries 1 chopper, good for minesweeping and
for getting those nasty subs.

Submarine.  [27,20]  Sneaks around, does good damage to ships.  Sinks
transports outright.  Can carry 1 special force.

Troop transport.  [11,9].  Carries a lot of stuff around pretty handily.
Armor, X, i, j, .....

Jeep.  [3,3].  Cheap first transport.  Carries money.

Carrier.  [40,30].  Ca

Battleship.  [45, 36].  Same as WWII period.

Guided Missle.  [15,5].  Powerful bomb that doesnt miss.

Atomic Bomb.  [100,10].  Same as WWII period - but notice it
takes a little less time to build.

Engineer.  [50 R+D, 20 Prod].  Produces villages, cities, or towns.  Can get 
you exponentially increasing production rates, if you live long enough.

Land fortifications:  Protects whatever city made it.

Village.  Small town.  Severely limited in its production, but produces 1
production resource per turn.

Bases.  Produces supplies and ammo, no money.
Towns.  Produces most units, supplies and ammo, and money.
Cities. Produces any unit, with less cost for the first unit of each type.

end{notes}

